    <CS_Studio_Variant_LayerRoleTip>Choose what this layer represents so runtime systems can decide when and how to treat it as a face, channel, or decorative layer.</CS_Studio_Variant_LayerRoleTip>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_Logic>Variant Logic</CS_Studio_Variant_Logic>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_LogicTip>Choose which runtime state decides the texture variant path for this layer. Hover the current mode to see what it matches.</CS_Studio_Variant_LogicTip>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_SectionHint>This section controls how the layer chooses texture variants under different preview contexts such as expression, facing, eye direction, blink, and frame sequence.</CS_Studio_Variant_SectionHint>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_BaseNameTip>Base name used when building variant texture paths. Leave empty to keep using the layer texture path directly.</CS_Studio_Variant_BaseNameTip>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_UseBlinkSuffix>Use Blink Suffix</CS_Studio_Variant_UseBlinkSuffix>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_UseBlinkSuffixTip>Append blink state suffixes to the variant lookup so the layer can switch textures during blink states.</CS_Studio_Variant_UseBlinkSuffixTip>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_UseDirectionalSuffix>Use Directional Suffix</CS_Studio_Variant_UseDirectionalSuffix>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_UseDirectionalSuffixTip>Append facing suffixes such as south, north, or eastwest when resolving this layer's variant path.</CS_Studio_Variant_UseDirectionalSuffixTip>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_DirectionalFacingTip>Restrict the layer to only render for a specific facing set. Use Any Facing to keep it available everywhere.</CS_Studio_Variant_DirectionalFacingTip>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_UseExpressionSuffix>Use Expression Suffix</CS_Studio_Variant_UseExpressionSuffix>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_UseExpressionSuffixTip>Append expression suffixes so the layer can swap textures for smile, angry, shock, and other expression states.</CS_Studio_Variant_UseExpressionSuffixTip>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_UseEyeDirectionSuffix>Use Eye Direction Suffix</CS_Studio_Variant_UseEyeDirectionSuffix>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_UseEyeDirectionSuffixTip>Append eye-direction suffixes so this layer can follow left, right, up, or down gaze variants.</CS_Studio_Variant_UseEyeDirectionSuffixTip>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_UseFrameSequence>Use Frame Sequence</CS_Studio_Variant_UseFrameSequence>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_UseFrameSequenceTip>Use numbered frame suffixes for animated variant sequences instead of a single static texture.</CS_Studio_Variant_UseFrameSequenceTip>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_VisibleExpressions>Visible Expressions</CS_Studio_Variant_VisibleExpressions>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_VisibleExpressionsTip>Comma-separated allowlist. When set, the layer only stays visible for the listed expressions.</CS_Studio_Variant_VisibleExpressionsTip>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_HiddenExpressionsTip>Comma-separated denylist. When set, the layer hides itself for the listed expressions.</CS_Studio_Variant_HiddenExpressionsTip>
    <CS_Studio_Variant_HideWhenMissingTip>Hide the layer instead of falling back when the resolved variant texture cannot be found.</CS_Studio_Variant_HideWhenMissingTip>
